Spray a large saucepan with oil and heat over a medium heat. Add the ginger, garlic and chillies and stir-fry for 1 minute.Add 1.7 litres/3 pints boiling water and bring to a simmer. Stir in the miso paste, lime juice and noodles and cook for 1 minute. Cover and set aside.Spray a large wok or frying pan with oil and stir-fry the chicken, mushrooms and sweetcorn for 2-3 minutes. Add the peas and cook for 2 minutes, or until the chicken is cooked through.Transfer the soup to 4 bowls, spoon over the vegetables and chicken. Top with watercress and serve with soy sauce on the side.